For those specializing in GPU architecture and performance engineering, tutorials range from foundational hardware principles to advanced driver and kernel optimization.
Foundational GPU Architecture
GPU Architectures and Programming (NPTEL): A comprehensive 12-week academic course covering streaming multiprocessors, cache hierarchy, and the graphics pipeline.
Arm Mali GPU Training: A specialized series focusing on mobile GPU architecture, hardware shader cores, and rendering pipelines.
Understanding GPU Architecture & Execution Model: A technical deep dive into hardware hierarchy, warp divergence, and memory coalescing. 
